# Cloudflare Pages _redirects
#
# This file configures how Pages handles incoming requests.
#
# ─── Worker API Proxy ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Route all /api/* requests to the NetPulse Worker.
# Replace the target URL with your actual deployed Worker URL.
#
# NOTE: If you use the Cloudflare Pages + Workers integration (binding the
# Worker directly in the Pages project dashboard), you do NOT need this file —
# the binding handles routing transparently. This file is only needed if the
# Worker is deployed as a standalone Workers service.
#
# Format: <source> <destination> <status-code>
#
# /api/*  https://netpulse-worker.YOUR-SUBDOMAIN.workers.dev/:splat  200
#
# ─── SPA Fallback ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# All unmatched routes return index.html so React Router handles client-side
# navigation. Must be the last rule.
/*  /index.html  200
